  "prompt": "What is it like to live in Mykonos, Greece?",
  "response": "Living in Mykonos, Greece offers a unique experience characterized by several key aspects:\n\n1. Climate\n- Mediterranean climate with hot, dry summers\n- Mild winters\n- Plenty of sunshine year-round\n\n2. Lifestyle\n- Vibrant and cosmopolitan atmosphere\n- Strong tourism-based economy\n- Lively nightlife and entertainment scene\n- Popular among international tourists and celebrities\n\n3. Culture\n- Traditional Greek island culture\n- Strong emphasis on hospitality\n- Rich history and beautiful architecture\n- Famous for white-washed buildings and windmills\n\n4. Cost of Living\n- Generally expensive, especially during peak tourist season\n- Higher prices for housing, food, and services\n- More affordable during off-peak months\n\n5. Economy\n- Heavily dependent on tourism\n- Seasonal work opportunities\n- Limited job market outside of tourism and hospitality\n\n6. Advantages\n- Beautiful beaches\n- Scenic landscapes\n- Relaxed Mediterranean lifestyle\n- Excellent seafood and Greek cuisine\n\n7. Challenges\n- Crowded during summer months\n- Limited job opportunities\n- High cost of living\n- Potential isolation during low season\n\nOverall, Mykonos offers a beautiful, vibrant lifestyle but can be challenging for long-term residents due to its tourism-driven economy and seasonal nature.",
